        <td bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>im curious as to insights regarding every class played at 60.  That is, with every spell, every tool the class gets.  Certain classes are and will always be pushovers, I dont see any way a mage can beat a necro, for example.  (killed one today by splurting and then chain Defluxing, was inneficient I know, but any caster class that is out-DDed by Deflux is just hopeless.)</P><P>Wizards, I would question whether we could be killed by.  Lure of Ice is 520 or so damage pvp, ToN is 450.  Assuming you have even remotely acceptable Fire Resistance (120+), and Sunstrike isnt an option, all they could do is Shock of Lightning/Lure of Ice over and over.  The big question is mana, but if you Demilich and chain ToN... Id imagine a 60 necro can get off enough Touch of Nights to kill even an epic wizard.</P><P>Shamen are my big question mark... they can be oom one minute, then Can IV a couple times and Torpor themselves.  Add in an unresistable manaless splurt effect on their epic, not to mention their pet...  I honestly dont think a necro can beat a well equipped shaman.  Best bet imo would be use siphon strength/shadow vortex/splurt over and over and null the shaman's epic effect or Vex to offset it.</P><P>What questions do we have?  and what solutions?  Big question I want answered is the shaman one, anyone have any better ideas for killing a shaman at 60?  They need never go oom, and never worry for health.  Add that together and even with Demilich we arent much of a match.</P><P>-Jalest<BR>rallos zek</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
