        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Zarloth</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'><BR>Shamans at level 60 are considered being very strong in PvP. They have a huge assortment of offensive and defensive spells, a (with buffs) strong pet, often a fungi tunic and maybe a regen spell that restores a lot of hps/tick, and they can melee a bit (against casters at least).</P><P>Best bet against a shaman is to find one of the ones that prefer to heal instead of dispelling / curing DoTs. </P><P>Slap pyro, splurt and vexing on them, and eventually they'll stagger and fall. But if they pumice DoTs, there's not much to be done since their heals are incredibly more efficient than necro DD taps.</P><P>Druids are pretty similar. They are dogmeat (no pun intended) if they don't dispell dots. I've fought a ton of druids lately and they fight in a very predictable manner. They open up with winged death and start running out of range, and then move back to cast scoriae. Feel free to start a druid PvP thread and I'll share my experiences.</P><P></P><P>Zarloth V`Sharatouum<BR>Vallon Zek<BR></font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Cerilius</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>A necro shouldn't have that much trouble beating a druid IMO. Deflux is 200/200 in PvP for 198 mana, Chloroblast is 428 for 175 mana, making Deflux only slightly less efficient than Chloroblast (taking into account the HP the druid will have to heal back from Deflux).</P><P>Don't bother trying to stack dots on a smart druid. Instead, go into lich form, dispel every dot, and tap every nuke (assuming your FR is good). Eventually you should both run OOM. Since Lich is 20/20 and Deflux is 200/200, this lets you win the fight. Just deflux every chance you get and hit the druid when he tries to med.</P><P>Cerilius</font></td>
